  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2009-05-14",
    "date": "2009-06-06T14:20:11Z",
    "text": "Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a taxpayer election to increase the tax credit for research expenditures by 20% for qualified energy research expenses incurred in 2009 or 2010. Defines \"qualified energy research expenses\" to include research expenses related to fuel cell and battery technology, renewable energy, energy conservation technology, electric transmission and distribution, and carbon capture and sequestration."
